programme.title: Happy Gilmore
programme.desc: Adam Sandler's second popular starring vehicle after Billy Madison is a goofy lowbrow paean to golf, hockey, and the comic hysterics of its childlike star. In Happy Gilmore, Sandler plays the title character, a raw, determined, but ultimately untalented hockey player who keeps trying out for the pros. When Happy discovers his grandmother (Frances Bay) will lose her home if she doesn't fork over 270,000 dollars to the IRS, he tries to figure out how he can possibly scrounge up the cash. An idea strikes during a game of one-upmanship with a couple furniture movers stripping his grandmother's home: On his first-ever swing, he drives a golf ball farther than the movers have ever seen. Before long, he has transplanted the foul-mouthed, aggressive persona of the hockey rink to the links, winning an amateur tourney that earns him a spot on the pro tour. Throttling everyone from a helpless caddy to game show host Bob Barker during the course of his 90-day quest to amass prize money, Happy also wins the sport a legion of new fans with his in-your-face style. Guiding him on his quest is a whimsical retired pro who lost his hand to an alligator (Carl Weathers) and an attractive public relations woman charmed by Happy's antics (Julie Bowen). Opposing him, however, is sneering hotshot Shooter McGavin (Christopher McDonald), who will do anything to win his championship jacket and see Happy fail(n)

programme.title: Futurama
programme.desc: A Bicyclops Built for Two. The Professor goes online using AOL, which has turned into a virtual reality experience. While in a chat room, Leela meets Alcazar, who claims to be a cyclops. She visits his planet and learns that they are the last two living cyclopses from the planet Cyclopia. After they spend the night together, Alcazar starts acting like a real jerk and the episode turns into a parody of Married...With Children with Alcazar as Al Bundy and Leela as Peggy Bundy . She accepts his marriage proposal while Fry and Bender find out that Alcazar is not a cyclops, but a shapeshifting alien who already proposed to four other women. It turns out he was just looking for wives to clean his castles while he made money by letting people watch(n)

programme.title: Futurama
programme.sub-title: How Hermes Requisitioned His Groove Back
programme.desc: How Hermes Requisitioned His Groove Back. Leela invites her old co-workers from the cryogenics lab over for a game of poker. When Bender uses x-ray specs to cheat, Leela's friends beat him up and inadvertently destroy Hermes' office. The anal-retentive Central Bureaucracy officer Morgan Proctor (voice of Nora Dunn) sees Hermes negligence and suspends him, appointing herself to take his place. Dr. Zoidberg suggests that Hermes spend some time at a health spa, but it turns out to be a slave labor camp. Meanwhile, Morgan tries to shape up the Planet Express offices and starts up a secret affair with Fry when she reveals her attraction to his slovenly ways. When Bender catches them, Morgan downloads his brain onto a disc and sends it to Central Bureaucracy. Finally, Hermes comes back and straightens everything out(n)

programme.title: Shallow Hal
programme.desc: Jack Black continues his march to stardom with this typical Farrelly brothers blend of broad comedy and a heartfelt message. Black is Hal Larsen, a shallow man rapidly approaching middle age whose superficiality can be attributed to his father's deathbed admonition to only date young, beautiful women. Hal and his best friend, Mauricio (Jason Alexander), have taken the advice to heart, but Hal finds all of his physically impressive girlfriends consistently lacking in other qualities that would make them ideal mates. When he bumps into self-help guru Tony Robbins (playing himself), the motivational entrepreneur is intrigued by Hal's predicament and hypnotizes him so that he'll only see the inner beauty of women. Hal is quickly smitten with Rosemary Shanahan (Gwyneth Paltrow), a blonde Peace Corps volunteer who's tenderhearted, funny, and intelligent. She is also gorgeous and meets Hal's basic criteria of outer perfection, but what he doesn't realize is that Robbins' spell is working and he cannot see that Rosemary actually weights 300 pounds. When Mauricio is finally able to snap Hal out of his charmed state, Hal's in love with the inwardly perfect woman and must overcome his obsession with beauty. The script for Shallow Hal (2001) was developed when Peter Farrelly enjoyed the humorous letters written to a mutual friend by Sean Moynihan, a computer software executive who followed the filmmaker's advice to take up screenwriting(n)

programme.title: Fantastic Four
programme.desc: Brilliant scientist Reed Richards builds a device that allows users to teleport to an alternate dimension, but an experiment involving it goes wrong and leaves him and his three teammates with unusual superpowers. The quartet are then forced to work together to battle an enemy from their past. This reboot of the iconic Marvel superhero team stars Miles Teller as Richards (who becomes Mr. Fantastic, able to bend and stretch his body into impossible shapes), Michael B. Jordan as Johnny Storm (aka the Human Torch, whose body can erupt in flames), Kate Mara as Sue Storm (aka the Invisible Woman -- no explanation needed), and Jamie Bell as Ben Grimm (who is transformed into the rock monster known as The Thing). Directed by Josh Trank, who previously worked with Jordan on the superhero film Chronicle(n)

programme.title: Double Take
programme.desc: Sharp-suited Daryl Johnson uncovers some financial chicanery in the accounts of a prestigious Mexican client. The next thing he knows is that he's been framed. A confused Daryl does the only thing he can: switch identities with gabbling hustler Freddy Tiffany(n)

programme.title: Stargate: The Ark of Truth
programme.desc: This feature-length follow-up to the action-packed series sees the SG-1 team embark on their deadliest mission yet. With the fate of Earth hanging in the balance, will they succeed?(n)

programme.title: The Ruins
programme.desc: Four American tourists unwisely venture off the beaten path while vacationing in Cancun. When a friendly German tourist implores the Americans to help search the jungle for his missing brother, the group becomes hopelessly trapped in a nightmare scenario that seems too strange to be true(n)

programme.title: Brown Sugar
programme.desc: Music writer Sidney and record producer Dre share a passion for hip-hop, but he's just married foxy Reese. Will the rap lovers ever get it together(n)

programme.title: Frailty
programme.desc: Fenton Meiks tells FBI agent Wesley Doyle a chilling story: his father was a serial killer who murdered people after hearing messages from God(n)

programme.title: 28 Weeks Later
programme.desc: Don, consumed by guilt after a run-in with the infected, arrives at London's Isle of Dogs where, with the help of the US Army, a safe haven has been established. But he must leave the safety of the compound after his two children escape to search for memories of their mother. Can Don save them from the blood rage and expunge his feelings of guilt?(n)

programme.title: Deception
programme.desc: A disconnected accountant finds his mundane life injected with a new sense of urgency after striking up a friendship with a charismatic attorney in director Marcel Langenegger's sexually charged action thriller. Jonathan (Ewan McGregor) is an accountant who has lost his passion in life. When his powerful new lawyer friend, Wyatt (Hugh Jackman), introduces Jonathan to a salacious underground sex club called The List, the dejected accountant soon believes he has found the woman of his dreams (Michelle Williams). His newfound happiness takes a turn for the worse, however, when Jonathan is named the prime suspect in the woman's disappearance as well as the theft of 20 million dollars(n)

programme.title: Jurassic World
programme.desc: Twenty-two years after Jurassic Park opened on Isla Nubar, a dinosaur-themed resort attracts thousands of visitors each year, just as John Hammond envisioned. However, following a bad sag in turnout a new effort is undertaken to revitalize Jurassic World, but once again mankind's attempts to interfere with nature bring ominous results(n)

programme.title: American Pie
programme.desc: A riotous and raunchy exploration of the passage to adulthood as Jim and his friends experience life, love and libido..(n)

programme.title: Vice Principals
programme.desc: The Field Trip. Danny wants to impress Amanda on a field trip organized by history teacher Mr. Hayden(n)

programme.title: The Boy Next Door
programme.desc: A lonely, recently divorced teacher has an affair with a much-younger man. However, their relationship takes a terrifying turn as he grows obsessed with her(n)

programme.title: Paper Towns
programme.desc: A nerdy teenager falls for the enigmatic girl next door, who vanishes after the two have an adventure together one night. She leaves behind a trail of clues, which lead him and his friends to go on a road trip to find her(n)

programme.title: Face Off
programme.desc: John Woo's action-packed thriller starring John Travolta and Nicholas Cage. When an FBI agent exchanges faces and identities with a terrorist, a deadly game of cat-and-mouse ensues(n)

programme.title: The Insider
programme.desc: A research chemist comes under personal and professional attack when he decides to appear in a "60 Minutes" expose on Big Tobacco(n)

programme.title: Jet Li's Fearless
programme.desc: Martial arts action based on the true story of the legendary Chinese hero Huo Yuan Jia, who seeks to rebuild his reputation after an error of judgment leads to his master's death. He learns that sportsmanship rather than brutality is the key to being a successful fighter(n)

programme.title: Stargate: Continuum
programme.desc: In a feature-length SG-1 special, Ba'al travels back in time and erases the Stargate programme from history. Can the team put the timeline back on track?(n)

programme.title: The Mistress of Spices
programme.desc: The life of Indian woman Tilo has been a real rollercoaster ride. She's been kidnapped by bandits, escaped from them, and has been trained in the noble art of using spices. Across the globe, in San Francisco, she opens her own store of spices and teaches her customers about the magical characteristics of spices. She follows three strict rules: to please her customers, but never get satisfied herself, to never leave the store and never let anyone touch her skin. But, when the charming architect Doug stops by her shop, all of the rules are suddenly hard to follow..(n)

programme.title: Ted 2
programme.desc: With the help of his best friend John, a sentient teddy bear named Ted fights to be legally recognized as a human so he can have a child with his new wife Tami-Lynn. This gut-busting comedy is a sequel to the 2012 surprise hit(n)

programme.title: Love & Basketball
programme.desc: Gina Prince-Bythewood wrote and directed this winning romantic drama about two young basketball stars. Omar Epps plays the cocky son of an NBA player; Sanaa Lathan is his tomboy girlfriend. Their relationship doesn't always go smoothly and, over the span of 15 years, they rebound from a number of romantic crises. Dennis Haysbert, Alfre Woodard(n)

programme.title: The 33
programme.desc: A gripping drama based on the true story of the mission to rescue 33 miners who were trapped in a underground mine for 69 days(n)

programme.title: Mafia!
programme.desc: Young Vincenzo Cortino, son of a Sicilian postman, travels to America to later become the clumsy chief of organized crime with his sons -- short-fused Joey and educated Anthony. One day, Tony makes a mistake and has to leave town. But when assassins try to do away with his father, he sets out for revenge(n)

programme.title: Mad Max: Fury Road
programme.desc: In a sun-parched future, loner Max gets caught up in the exodus of a clan of rebels fleeing an evil despot as they race across the Wasteland(n)

programme.title: Trespass
programme.desc: Two Arkansas firemen learn from a dying man that he hid a stash of gold in a disused warehouse 50 years earlier in an East St Louis ghetto. When they go in search of the loot, the pair unwittingly observe a murder carried out by the local mob and become targets themselves, especially when it becomes known why they happen to be in the area in the first place(n)

programme.title: Ted 2
programme.desc: With the help of his best friend John, a sentient teddy bear named Ted fights to be legally recognized as a human so he can have a child with his new wife Tami-Lynn. This gut-busting comedy is a sequel to the 2012 surprise hit(n)

programme.title: The Brothers Grimm
programme.desc: In Terry Gilliam's inventive fantasy, the famed authors are cast as con artists who get caught up in a real-life fairy tale involving a haunted forest where girls have been disappearing. Matt Damon and Heath Ledger star in this whimsical adventure. Jonathan Pryce, Monica Bellucci, Peter Stormare, Lena Headey(n)

programme.title: Vacation
programme.desc: In this hilarious installment of the "Vacation" series, the youngest son of the Griswold clan, now grown with a family of his own, sets out to re-create a cross-country road trip from his youth to an amusement park(n)

programme.title: One Hour Photo
programme.desc: An alienated photo developer's obsession with an ordinary family culminates in his bizarre confrontation with the unfaithful father(n)

programme.title: Carlito's Way
programme.desc: Al Pacino's gritty performance propels this saga about a former drug lord's efforts to go straight(n)

programme.title: Making of 'Maze Runner: The Scorch Trials'
programme.desc: A look at "Maze Runner: The Scorch Trials," the 2015 sequel to "The Maze Runner" (2014) in which Thomas, Teresa, and the rest of the Gladers prepare for phase two of their trials after narrowly escaping the first test. The film stars Dylan O'Brien, Kaya Scodelario and Thomas Brodie-Sangster, and is directed by Wes Ball(n)

programme.title: El amor me queda grande
programme.desc: A 10-year-old boy is in love with a girl two years older who won't let anything stop her from becoming a wealthy writer and critic(n)

programme.title: The Astronaut's Wife
programme.desc: Rand Ravich's sci-fi thriller stars Johnny Depp (soon to be seen as J M Barrie in Neverland ) as a Nasa astronaut who loses all contact for two minutes while on a space-walk. Successfully rescued and back on Earth, he gives up his career to join a large corporation, much to the relief of his wife Charlize Theron (soon to be seen in Reindeer Games ). But, as he starts to act more strangely, she begins to wonder what actually happened in those 120 seconds and what this could mean for their unborn child(n)

programme.title: The Tailor of Panama
programme.desc: A disgraced British operative is dispatched to Central America, where a suit maker he prods into spying for him fabricates a story about a political insurrection(n)

programme.title: The Theory of Everything
programme.desc: James Marsh's biopic of the celebrated scientist Stephen Hawking, The Theory of Everything, stars Eddie Redmayne as the famous figure. Enrolled as a graduate student at Cambridge, Hawking establishes himself as one of the leading minds of his generation, and begins to win the heart of Jane (Felicity Jones). After one of his earliest breakthroughs, Hawking is diagnosed with ALS, and he becomes less and less able to control his own body. With the loyal Jane at his side, he continues his work. However, as the years progress, Jane starts to feel more like a nurse than a wife, and Hawking begins to have feelings for a woman who is hired to care for him. The Theory of Everything screened at the 2014 Toronto International Film Festival(n)

programme.title: A Beautiful Mind
programme.desc: Oscar-winning drama based on the true story of prominent mathematician John Forbes Nash Jr, who seemed to be guaranteed a promising future when he won international acclaim as a result of his pioneering work in the field. However, when he is recruited to provide assistance to the military with top-secret code-breaking duties, the high-pressure job takes its toll on him and he begins to develop a mental illness. Dir: Ron Howard(n)

programme.title: Other People's Money
programme.desc: A satirical look at the values of 1980s America, based on the popular off-Broadway play. An unscrupulous Wall Street asset stripper sees his chance to make a fast buck with the takeover and break-up of a small but profitable family-run company. The laid-back owner has no intention of selling, however, and calls in a talented lawyer who is as manipulative as the money-grabbing adversary she attempts to out-manoeuvre(n)

programme.title: Wall Street
programme.desc: Oliver Stone's morality tale stars Charlie Sheen as Bud Fox, an ambitious young stockbroker, who's willing to do whatever it takes to emulate his hero, supremely wealthy financier Gordon Gekko. Bud's initial attempts to play the market honestly don't light his touchpaper to success. But, when he passes on some insider information to Gekko, his career starts to pick up pace and, as he becomes increasingly embroiled in illegal trading and financial espionage, he begins to make the money of his dreams. However, he fails to fully comprehend the true cost of his deals until one of them threatens the livelihood of his union boss father. Also starring Daryl Hannah and Terence Stamp(n)

programme.title: The Martian
programme.desc: A lone astronaut is left behind on the hostile surface of Mars after an exploratory mission goes awry, and must use his ingenuity to create a habitat where he can survive. Meanwhile, his crewmates and a team of scientists work to rescue him, in defiance of NASA protocol(n)

programme.title: Scarface
programme.desc: A Cuban immigrant becomes a cocaine kingpin in this update on the gangland classic(n)

programme.title: The Wrestler
programme.desc: Mickey Rourke stars as a former professional-wrestling superstar fallen on hard times and grappling with a rocky personal life while looking for a chance at a comeback in the ring(n)

programme.title: Focus
programme.desc: A con artist takes on an inexperienced apprentice, but struggles to keep his eyes on the prize when he develops romantic feelings for her(n)

programme.title: Wonder Woman
programme.desc: A graceful Amazon princess of untold strength and beauty attempts to prevent the god of war from instigating a conflict that will last for centuries and destroy the human race as the animated adventure marking the return of DC Comics heroine Wonder Woman. On the mystical island of Themyscira lives a fierce race of warrior Amazons who have raised a powerful daughter named Princess Diana. The Amazons live in secrecy from the outside world, but when Army fighter pilot Steve Travor crash-lands in their tropical paradise, the headstrong princess defies the law of the land by accompanying Trevor back to civilization. But her transition into the modern world won't be an easy one, because when Ares escapes from his Amazonian prison and begins plotting his revenge, Princess Diana is the only person who stands between the god of war, and the destruction of the human race - beginning with the Amazons. Now, as Princess Diana harnesses her unique powers to boldly fight back against Ares and save the planet from certain destruction, Wonder Woman is born and the battle for civilization begins(n)

programme.title: Balls of Fury
programme.desc: An ex-ping pong champion is persuaded by the FBI to go undercover at an underground table tennis tournament, where he comes face-to-face with his dad's fiendishly evil murderer(n)

programme.title: Code Name: The Cleaner
programme.desc: Cedric the Entertainer is a riot as an amnesiac who gets mixed up with secret agents, a mysterious femme fatale (Nicollette Sheridan) and a high-level conspiracy in this hilarious spy spoof. Lucy Liu, Mark Dacascos, Callum Keith Rennie. Directed by Les Mayfield(n)

programme.title: Lucky Numbers
programme.desc: John Travolta plays Russ Richards, a small-town weatherman who is such a local celebrity that he even has his own table at the local Denny's. He obviously sees himself as a big deal about town, and he's got the spending habits to prove it, including payments on a big house and a fancy Jaguar. His unstable life is further complicated by the fling he's having with the station's lotto girl, who is also having an affair with the married station manager(n)

programme.title: The Brothers McMullen
programme.desc: Director: Edward Burns. Three Irish Catholic brothers from Long Island struggle to deal with love, marriage, and infidelity(n)

programme.title: What Happens in Vegas
programme.desc: Career woman Joy heads off to Las Vegas to cheer herself up after being very publicly dumped by her boyfriend. Fate leads her to meeting amiable slacker Jack and the new friends soon enjoy a boozy evening. Later that evening, rather drunk, they end up getting hitched. As reality dawns the next morning, the duo plan to divorce as quickly as they married. But Jack wins a massive amount of money, after putting one of Joy's coins in a slot machine. Their squabble over the money leads to a judge freezing the assets and sentencing them to make a go of their marriage - for at least six months. Tom Vaughan's romantic comedy also stars Queen Latifah as the marriage guidance expert who tries to keep the couple together(n)

programme.title: Fracture
programme.desc: Anthony Hopkins, as a diabolical homicide suspect, and Ryan Gosling as the dogged prosecutor on his tail are equally fascinating as they engage in a deadly game of cat and mouse in this absorbing legal thriller. Hopkins is a brilliant engineer who is literally trying to get away with murder---his wife's---and Gosling is the DA whose case is not as open-and-shut as he thought it would be. Directed by Gregory Hoblit(n)

programme.title: Under Siege
programme.desc: Casey Ryback is a former Navy SEAL captain who is now the cook aboard the USS Missouri. Everyone aboard is about to celebrate the birthday of Captain Adams. They've even hired a band led by William Strannix, and former playboy playmate Jordan Tate to jump out of a cake and dance. What Adams doesn't know is that he is in for a deadly surprise(n)

Sin City author Frank Miller's sweeping take on the historic Battle of Thermopylae comes to the screen courtesy of Dawn of the Dead director Zack Snyder. Gerard Butler stars as Spartan King Leonidas and Lena Headey plays Queen Gorgo. The massive army of the Persian Empire is sweeping across the globe, crushing every force that dares stand in its path. When a Persian envoy arrives in Sparta offering King Leonidas power over all of Greece if he will only bow to the will of the all powerful Xerxes (Rodrigo Santoro), the strong-willed leader assembles a small army comprised of his empire's best fighters and marches off to battle. Though they have virtually no hope of defeating Xerxes' intimidating battalion, Leonidas' men soldier on, intent on letting it be known they will bow to no man but their king. Meanwhile, back in Sparta, the loyal Queen Gorgo attempts to convince both the skeptical council and the devious Theron (Dominic West) to send more troops despite the fact that many view Leonidas' unsanctioned war march as a serious transgression. As Xerxes' fearsome "immortals" draw near, a few noble Greeks vow to assist the Spartans on the battlefield. When King Leonidas and his 300 Spartan warriors fell to the overwhelming Persian army at the Battle of Thermopylae, the fearless actions of the noble fighters inspired all of Greece to stand up against their Persian enemy and wage the battle that would ultimately give birth to the modern concept of democracy(n)

programme.title: Frank Miller's Sin City
programme.desc: Three flawed individuals search for a violent justice on the rain-soaked, crime-ridden streets of Basin City(n)

programme.title: Outcast

programme.title: Outcast
programme.desc: What Lurks Within. Rev. Anderson becomes increasingly alienated; Sidney's revelation stuns Kyle(n)

programme.title: What We Do in the Shadows
programme.desc: Flight of the Conchords collaborators Jemaine Clement and Taika Waititi reteam for this comical mock-documentary centering on four contemporary vampire roommates waging an immortal struggle to be cool. When they're not looking for their next meal or scheming to get into the hottest dance clubs, the bloodsucking foursome get their kicks by stirring up trouble with the local lycanthropes, or bickering to determine who's fallen behind on their housework. Rhys Darby, Jonathan Brugh, Stu Rutherford and Jackie van Beek co-star(n)

programme.title: Gentlemen Broncos
programme.desc: This lovable, offbeat comedy centers on sad-sack teenager Benjamin (Michael Angarano), who attends a writing workshop to pursue his dream of becoming a fantasy novelist. However, a famous author (Jemaine Clement) at the workshop steals his material. Directed by Jared Hess. Jennifer Coolidge, Sam Rockwell, Mike White(n)

programme.title: Borat: Cultural Learnings of America for Make Benefit Glorious Nation of Kazakhstan
programme.desc: Mockumentary following the misadventures of Borat, a Kazakh journalist, as he interacts with real people on a road trip across America as he seeks to marry Pamela Anderson(n)

programme.title: Blazing Saddles
programme.desc: A send-up of Hollywood Westerns finds a railroad slated to be diverted through an existing town, and a crooked Attorney General forcing a dimwitted governor to appoint a black sheriff to horrify the townsfolk, who all have the same last name(n)

programme.title: Death Defying Acts
programme.desc: Catherine Zeta-Jones and Guy Pearce display a mesmerizing screen magic in this intriguing romantic drama set in 1926 Edinburgh. Zeta-Jones plays a beautiful con artist who poses as a fake medium to bilk illusionist Harry Houdini (Pearce), who has offered $10,000 to any psychic who can conjure up his late mother's final words. While getting to know the grifter, the famous escape artist begins to develop a personal attachment to her. Saoirse Ronan. Directed by Gillian Armstrong(n)

programme.title: O Brother, Where Art Thou?
programme.desc: In this update of Homer's "The Odyssey," set in the 1930's Depression-era deep South, three convicts - the garrulous silver-tongued Everett, the sweet and simple Delmar and the maladjusted Pete - escape from a chain gang and embark on the adventure of a lifetime(n)

programme.title: Cop Land
programme.desc: James Mangold's thriller stars Sylvester Stallone in one of his best roles, as Freddy Heflin, the sheriff of Garrison, a small town in New Jersey. But Garrison is also home to a group of corrupt New York cops, led by Ray Donlan, who protects his own when two innocent young men are shot by a drunken rookie. Heflin's only hope of getting justice is to team up with Moe Tilden of Internal Affairs. Also starring Ray Liotta(n)

programme.title: Birdman or (The Unexpected Virtue of Ignorance)
programme.desc: A fading actor, best known for his portrayal of a superhero, plans a comeback by appearing in a Broadway play. However, his attempts to become more altruistic, rebuild his career and reconnect with friends and family prove more difficult than expected(n)

programme.title: El Cantante
programme.desc: Pop icon Marc Anthony steps into the role of Salsa superstar Hector Lavoe in this biopic that follows the singer from his early career success as a Puerto Rican teen sensation to his later status as a New York City Latin idol while also documenting his ongoing struggle against drug and alcohol addiction. Actress and pop star Jennifer Lopez co-stars as Puchi; Lavoe's longtime muse and love interest(n)

programme.title: Batman Returns
programme.desc: The world's most enigmatic superhero, Batman, resurfaces for another Gotham City adventure. programme.title: Hitman: Agent 47
programme.desc: In this action-packed thriller, a mysterious, superhuman assassin teams with a young woman to take down a major corporation plotting to use his genetic makeup to create a race of unstoppable killers(n)

programme.title: Scream
programme.desc: Wes Craven's clever spoof of '80s slasher films is about a killer who targets a teen (Neve Campbell) whose mother was brutally murdered the year before(n)

programme.desc: An air-traffic controller (Chevy Chase) is having the worst luck: first his girlfriend leaves him, and then he experiences a nuclear disaster. His life begins to pick up after he realizes that the radiation fallout has given him magical telekinetic powers. He decides to settle a few scores with his new-found power(n)

programme.title: House
programme.desc: Director Robby Henson's psychological thriller House concerns a husband and wife who, attempting to patch up their marriage after the death of their child, decide on a spur of the moment to ignore their regularly scheduled therapy session and set off on a trip. After a car accident incapacitates their vehicle, the duo ends up at the title dwelling, where they meet another couple as well as the off-putting people who own the establishment. programme.title: Avengers: Age of Ultron
programme.desc: This sequel to the smash-hit comic-book epic The Avengers finds the iconic superhero team dealing with a threat of their own making: a sentient robot called Ultron (voice of James Spader), who was originally designed as part of a peacekeeping program. Since the events of the last film, Captain America (Chris Evans), Iron Man (Robert Downey Jr.), the Hulk (Mark Ruffalo), Thor (Chris Hemsworth), Hawkeye (Jeremy Renner), and Black Widow (Scarlett Johansson) have been working to take down various cells of a secret society of villains known as HYDRA. Their zeal to make the world a better, safer place inspires Tony Stark, genius billionaire and alter ego of Iron Man, to create Ultron in order to respond to additional threats that the Avengers aren't able to handle. Ultron, unfortunately, takes this directive way too seriously -- he believes that world peace can only be achieved by exterminating humanity, and he'll stop at nothing to accomplish this goal. The battle between the Avengers and Ultron is further complicated by the appearance of superpowered siblings Quicksilver (Aaron Taylor-Johnson) and Scarlet Witch (Elizabeth Olsen), who ally themselves with the homicidal android. Samuel L. Jackson and Cobie Smulders co-star as, respectively, S.H.I.E.L.D. operatives Nick Fury and Maria Hill. Joss Whedon, writer and director of the previous Avengers movie, returns in both capacities here(n)

programme.title: On the Record With Greta Van Susteren
programme.desc: As part of the ongoing ratings war between rival cable services CNN and The Fox News Network, CNN commentator Greta Van Susteren was wooed to the "other network" with promises of a much larger salary and a nightly interview program of her own. That program, On the Record With Greta Van Susteren, debuted on February 4, 2002. While some observers were mildly surprised that Van Susteren, whose politics tended to be left of center, would agree to star on a cable network with a perceived Conservative slant, most of the press attention concerning the new series was focused on Van Susteren's remarkable cosmetic-surgery makeover, which she insisted had been decided upon long before Fox News Network offered her a job. On the Record With Greta Van Susteren was seen on a Monday through Friday basis from 10:00 to 11:00 p.m. EST

That program, On the Record With Greta Van Susteren, debuted on February 4, 2002. While some observers were mildly surprised that Van Susteren, whose politics tended to be left of center, would agree to star on a cable network with a perceived Conservative slant, most of the press attention concerning the new series was focused on Van Susteren's remarkable cosmetic-surgery makeover, which she insisted had been decided upon long before Fox News Network offered her a job.
